reviews.review_text: Good one. Wonderful show. Rock solid. This upgrade is the ticket.  I cannot say enough about the Scarlet>Fire.....intricate,exploratory, and nice and long. It is one of the best I believe my ears have heard.....Check out what I will call the "Jello Jam".  I swear Bobby will whammy bar you senseless during the transition ...everybody is just going full on but coming together oh so serendipitously, on this one.  They pull out all the extra bells,whistles, tinkle-sprinkles, echo effects and such...The Fire is a smoke-show!!  2nd set just keeps on a blazing away with a pounding Samson and a beautiful He's Gone, and so on......So many hot shows in 1983---especially the latter part, in my opinion.  Check out back in mid-October if you need a pointer to a few more hot ones from this era.

Wow! I saw this link from @deadheadland. It brought my new favorite Scarlet-Fire. + You get to watch it.
http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ez5oslnpc6s&feature=related. I will be seeking more 83's.
